The paper is about creating datasets for image harmonization, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves image processing and graphics (cs.GR), as well as machine learning (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.LG) techniques for image harmonization. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of existing datasets such as COCO and Adobe5k, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
